result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan C Newsome was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:07 PM Defendant Jordan C Newsome in court, in custody with attorney Nick Dalla Santa.  Brenda L. Yaskal appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Probation Agent Jennifer Jordan appeared. All parties appeared by Zoom. Cases called: 15CF181 & 15CF314. State argued for prison time and consecutive sentences. Right to be present recited, waived. Atty Dalla Santa argued for less prison time and a concurrent sentence. Statement by defendant. Court sentenced the defendant in 15CF181 to serve 7 years in prison, consecutive to any other sentence currently serving, 3 years initial confinement and 4 years extended supervision. 472 days credit. In 15CF314 Court sentenced the defendant to serve 4 years in prision, 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision consecutive to 15CF181. 91 days jail credit. A civil judgment will be entered for the unpaid financial obligations. Defendant is not eligible for the challenge incarceration program or the substance abuse program. 3:42 PM
